npc/rina: You want to understand what the Collector is. I can tell you.
npc/rina: Before she was part of this system, she was a debt collector for the gambling platform's loan arm — the pinjol side.
npc/rina: Here is how the trap closes. The platform extends credit to players who've run out. Small amounts. Then larger. The interest compounds every single day.
npc/rina: A loan of Rp1,000,000 can become Rp3,000,000 in weeks. People borrow from a second app to pay the first. Then a third. It's a spiral with no floor.
npc/rina: She was the one who called. Who showed up. Who spammed every contact in the phone — family, neighbours, employers — until the debt was paid.
npc/rina: She never asked whether the debt was fair. Only whether it was owed.
npc/rina: When the platform migrated into this network, she came with it. Willingly, from what I understand.
npc/rina: She does not need a body anymore. She IS the debt — a process that runs endlessly, searching for accounts marked unpaid.
npc/rina: Everyone who ever borrowed to keep gambling and could not repay is in her registry. She does not forget. She does not expire.
npc/rina: And she is getting closer to this part of the network.
